-- Dodgers Get Gonzalez, Crawford, Beckett in Trade With Red Sox
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-08-25T21:13:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-25/dodgers-get-gonzalez-crawford-beckett-in-trade-with-red-sox.html
The Los Angeles Dodgers acquired
Adrian Gonzalez,  Carl Crawford  and Josh Beckett as part of a
nine-player trade with the Boston Red Sox.  The Dodgers said in a news release they also receive
infielder Nick Punto and an undisclosed amount of money from
Boston in exchange for first baseman James Loney, pitcher Allen
Webster, infielder Ivan De Jesus and two players to be named
later.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  